FT  15 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Pressure on margins at Polar
POLAR, the USM-quoted electronic components distributor, reported a marginal
decrease - from Pounds 917,000 to Pounds 902,000 - over the 12 months to
October 2.
Mr Keith Carnelley, chairman, said that 'very difficult trading conditions'
had prevailed for the third successive year with reduced demand and
'unprecedented pressure' on margins.
Nevertheless the group increased its market share with sales ahead 13 per
cent to Pounds 17.4m.
Earnings per share emerged at 7.3p (7.4p); a recommended final dividend of
2.5p maintains the total for the year at 4.5p.
